  "prompt": "How many ways are there to pronounce Quora?",
  "response": "\"Quora\" is typically pronounced in a couple of main ways, though slight variations may exist based on regional accents or personal preferences. Here are the most common pronunciations:\n\n1. **\"KWO-ra\"** (rhymes with \"flora\"):\n   - **IPA:** /\u02c8kw\u0254\u02d0r\u0259/ or /\u02c8kw\u0254\u02d0r\u0259/\n   - This pronunciation emphasizes a \"kwaw\" sound at the beginning, similar to the word \"cower\" without the \"er.\"\n\n2. **\"KWAH-ra\"**:\n   - **IPA:** /\u02c8kw\u0251\u02d0r\u0259/\n   - In this variant, the first syllable sounds like \"kwah,\" with a more open \"ah\" vowel sound.\n\nWhile these are the primary ways people pronounce \"Quora,\" slight deviations can occur based on individual accents or dialects. However, both pronunciations are widely understood and accepted.",
